I visited the Netherlands twice last year, and I only saw the area around the central station in Amsterdam.  It was raining and crowded, and there was gum all over the sidewalks..  I’m sure I missed the nicer areas of Amsterdam.   I spent most of my time in the small towns in Overijssel, and those areas were a paradise compared to America (and maybe compared to anywhere).

I was convinced the Netherlands is where I wanted to retire .  But now I’m having second thoughts because of the climate and how expensive the housing is..  even in the 2000+ range it’s hard to find a house or an apartment with two beds and two baths.   I realize you get what you pay for, but I want to have some money left over to take vacations, lol..
